INTRODUCTION
A Risk Management Plan has been implemented at Norfolk Southern's East End Shop facility for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials.  This Management Plan summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to the community of hazardous chemical releases.  The Plan summary is organized to correspond with specific Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP definitions and requirements, including:

7 Introduction;
7 Norfolk Southern statement of commitment to protect health, environment, and safety;
7 Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
7 Hazard Assessment;
7 Five-Year Accident History;
7 Emergency Response Plan; and
7 Planned changes to improve safety

NORFOLK SOUTHERN COMMITMENT TO PROTECT HEALTH, ENVIRONMENT, AND SAFTETY 
Norfolk Southern Railway Company is committed to the safe and environmentally responsible handling of hazardous materials.  Norfolk Southern's goal is to manage risks associated with hazardous materials and to efficiently respond to incidents involving hazardous materials.  This RMP formalizes and documents these activities.  

FACILITY IDENTIFICATION AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES COVERED PROCESSES 
The East End Shops facility is located at 8 = Street at Campbell Avenue, Roanoke, Roanoke County, Virginia 24042.  Propylene is used in the car shop facility for welding torches and space heating and is regulated under 40 CFR Part 68, the EPA Risk Management Program (RMP) Rule.  The propylene process at East End Shops, which includes four (4) 1,000 gallon tanks (equivalent to 15,136 pounds), is the only process that exceeds the 10,000-pound RMP threshold.

